# 1. Install Jest and TypeScript Support
npm install --save-dev jest ts-jest @types/jest

# 2. Create a configuration file named jest.config.js at the same level as package.json by running:
npx ts-jest config:init

# 3. This command will create a basic Jest configuration file. Edit the file to include the following code:
module.exports = {
  preset: "ts-jest",
  testEnvironment: "node"
};

# 5. Create a folder named tests at the same level as package.json and place your test files under this folder. Test files should follow the naming convention {file_name}.test.ts.

# 6. You can now run your tests using:
npm test
# or
npx jest